# Routes all @facioquo/* packages to GitHub Packages registry.
# Required for installing packages published there (e.g., from facioquo/design-system)
# and for the publish-time version check in CI workflows.
#
# Auth is NOT stored here. pnpm v10+ does not expand ${ENV_VAR} in project-level
# .npmrc (security hardening), so credentials must live in a trusted location:
#   - Local dev:  pnpm config set "//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken" "$(gh auth token)"
#                 (writes to ~/.npmrc — never commit a token)
#   - CI:         actions/setup-node with registry-url writes a user-level .npmrc
#                 from NODE_AUTH_TOKEN automatically.
@facioquo:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
